<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1939-04-11T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1939-04-11T17:00:00-05:00" n="797" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d797">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">867N.01/1515a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Minister in Egypt</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Fish</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1939-04-11T17:00:00-05:00">April 11, 1939—5
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>19. Please comment by telegraph on a press report that Dr. Weizmann,
                                President of the World Zionist Organization, has arrived in Cairo at
                                the invitation of the Egyptian Government, that the Egyptian
                                Ambassador has brought from London new British proposals for
                                Palestine and that a new conference might be held looking to a
                                settlement of Jewish-Arab differences. The presence in Cairo is also
                                reported of the Emir Feisal<note n="53" xml:id="d797fn53">Eldest son
                                    of Ibn Saud; Foreign Minister for Saudi Arabia.</note> and Iraq
                                and Palestine delegates.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>